========================================================================
CLAIM 2: delta_p definition and positivity
========================================================================

  DEFINITION (from paper):
    delta_p = -log(||p*pi/10||) - log(p)

  LEMMA: For p in S, delta_p > 0.
  PROOF: ||p*pi/10|| < 1/p  =>  -log(||p*pi/10||) > log(p)
         =>  delta_p = -log(||p*pi/10||) - log(p) > 0.  QED.

  Verification for S_4 = {2,3,19,191}:
    p=   2: ||2*pi/10|| = 0.371681469282  < 1/2 = 0.500000000000? True  =>  delta_2 = 0.29657088 > 0? True
    p=   3: ||3*pi/10|| = 0.057522203923  < 1/3 = 0.333333333333? True  =>  delta_3 = 1.75697196 > 0? True
    p=  19: ||19*pi/10|| = 0.030973958179  < 1/19 = 0.052631578947? True  =>  delta_19 = 0.53016951 > 0? True
    p= 191: ||191*pi/10|| = 0.004419683565  < 1/191 = 0.005235602094? True  =>  delta_191 = 0.16941375 > 0? True

  Definition and positivity: VERIFIED.

========================================================================
CLAIM 3: Individual delta_p values (paper vs truth)
========================================================================

  CRITICAL FINDING: The paper has TWO independent errors in delta_p:
  ERROR A) Wrong ||p*pi/10|| values (from Claim 1)
  ERROR B) SIGN ERROR: paper computes -log(||.||) + log(p)  [uses +]
           but the DEFINITION uses -log(||.||) - log(p)      [uses -]

      p   paper -log(||.||)  paper sign   paper log(p)   paper delta    TRUE delta        diff  verdict
  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
      2            0.989644           +       0.693147      1.682791      0.296571      1.3862  WRONG
         TRUE -log(||.||) = 0.989718  SIGN = -  TRUE log(p) = 0.693147

      3            2.854428           +       1.098612      3.953040      1.756972      2.1961  WRONG
         TRUE -log(||.||) = 2.855584  SIGN = -  TRUE log(p) = 1.098612

     19            3.497762           +       2.944439      6.442201      0.530170      5.9120  WRONG
         TRUE -log(||.||) = 3.474608  SIGN = -  TRUE log(p) = 2.944439

    191            6.466605           +       5.252273     11.718878      0.169414     11.5495  WRONG
         TRUE -log(||.||) = 5.421687  SIGN = -  TRUE log(p) = 5.252273


  NOTE: The sign error alone (using + instead of -):
  If we used the wrong sign but CORRECT ||.|| values:
    p=2: -log(CORRECT ||.||) + log(p) = 1.682865  vs paper 1.682791  diff=0.000074
    p=3: -log(CORRECT ||.||) + log(p) = 3.954197  vs paper 3.953040  diff=0.001157
    p=19: -log(CORRECT ||.||) + log(p) = 6.419047  vs paper 6.442201  diff=0.023154
    p=191: -log(CORRECT ||.||) + log(p) = 10.673961  vs paper 11.718878  diff=1.044917

